    "Id": "chassisdef_mongrel_MGL-T1",
    "Name": "Mongrel",
    "Details": "Designed with a hybrid of Inner Sphere and Clan technologies, the MGL-T1's noted speed comes from its 350 XL engine. This powerful Clan-tech engine allowed the swift 'Mech to outpace most machines on the battlefield with a top speed of 118.8 km/h. Its endo steel hull is protected by 10.5 tons of reactive armor, giving it additional protection from area-effect weapons, penetrating weapons, and missile fire. The Mongrel' T1 model weaponry includes three Clan ER medium lasers fitted to its right torso. Backing up these up is an AC/5, the autocannon is supplied with 20 rounds of ammunition found in its one-ton ammunition bin. The Mongrel has a retractable blade mounted in its right arm actuator, in case the pilot needs to engage in melee combat.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Easy to Pilot</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.1</color></b>\n\n<br><br><color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limit: Left Upper</color>",
